- **Install MongoDB**: `sudo apt-get install -y mongodb`
- **Start MongoDB Service**: `sudo service mongod start`
- **Install Node.js**: `curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_16.x | sudo -E bash - && sudo apt-get install -y nodejs`
- **Create a New Project**: `mkdir myapp && cd myapp`
- **Initialize npm**: `npm init -y`
- **Install Express and MongoDB Driver**: `npm install express mongodb`
- **Key Config Options**:
  - `app.set('port', process.env.PORT || 3000);` for setting the port
  - `mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost:27017/mydatabase');` for connecting to MongoDB
- **Example Code Snippet**:
  ```javascript
  const express = require('express');
  const mongoose = require('mongoose');
  const app = express();

  // Connect to MongoDB
  mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost:27017/mydatabase', { useNewUrlParser: true, useUnifiedTopology: true });

  // Define a schema and model
  const UserSchema = new mongoose.Schema({ name: String });
  const User = mongoose.model('User', UserSchema);

  // Create a route to get all users
  app.get('/users', async (req, res) => {
    try {
      const users = await User.find();
      res.json(users);
    } catch (error) {
      res.status(500).json({ message: error.message });
    }
  });

  // Start the server
  app.listen(app.get('port'), () => {
    console.log(`Server is running on port ${app.get('port')}`);
  });
  ```
- **Run the Server**: `node app.js`
- **Test API**: Use tools like Postman or curl to test your API endpoints.

